  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "15. Greet—\"Salute them that love us in the faith.\" All at Crete had not this love rooted in faith, the true bond of fellowship. A salutation peculiar to this Epistle, such as no forger would have used.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Grace—Greek, \"The grace,\" namely, of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with you all—not that the Epistle is addressed to all the Cretan Christians, but Titus would naturally impart it to his flock.   ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
