        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 1:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is that which binds Christians together more or less closely. Timothy and Titus were St. Paul’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τέκνα ἐν πίστει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; others were more distantly related to him, though of the same family, “the household of faith”.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
